bibliography data in addition to title and abstract on text classification performance for automatic citation screening."}]}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "as020", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "st110"}, "_": "Methods"}, {"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "sp020", "view": "all"}, "_": "We experiment with binary and Word2vec feature representations and SVM models using 4 software engineering (SE) and 15 medical review datasets. We build and compare 3 types of models (binary-non-linear, Word2vec-linear and Word2vec-non-linear kernels) with each dataset using the two feature sets."}]}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "as025", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "st115"}, "_": "Results"}, {"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "sp025", "view": "all"}, "_": "The bibliography enriched data exhibited consistent improved performance in terms of recall, work saved over sampling (WSS) and Matthews correlation coefficient (MCC) in 3 of the 4 SE datasets that are fairly large in size. For the medical datasets, the results vary, however in the majority of cases the performance is the same or better."}]}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "as030", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "st120"}, "_": "Conclusion"}, {"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "sp030", "view": "all"}, "_": "Inclusion of the bibliography data provides the potential of improving the performance of the models but to date results are inconclusive."}]}]}]}}